    • Method Detail

      • addCell

        void addCell(ec.util.MersenneTwisterFast random,
             Simulation sim)
        Adds a cell to the simulation.

        The cell location is split, along with any tagged regions. The new cell is created, initialized, and added to the schedule. Both cells are reset remain in the proliferative state.

        Parameters:
        random - the random number generator
        sim - the simulation instance

      • checkpointG1

        void checkpointG1()
        Checkpoints transition between G1 and S phase.

        Checkpoints include:

        • Cell growth: cell size must be at least GROWTH_CHECKPOINT_G1 times the critical size

        Cells that do not pass the cell growth checkpoint become arrested.

      • checkpointG2

        void checkpointG2()
        Checkpoints transition between G2 and M phase.

        Checkpoints include:

        • Cell growth: cell size must be at least GROWTH_CHECKPOINT_G2 times the critical size

        Cells that do not pass the cell growth checkpoint become arrested.

      • stepG1

        void stepG1(double r)
        Performs actions for G1 phase.

        Cell increases in size toward a target of twice its critical size. Cell will transition to S phase after an average time of DURATION_G1. Between G1 and S phase, cell must pass a checkpoint.

        For cells arrested in G1, the transition check for checkpoint recovery occurs after an average time of DURATION_CHECKPOINT.

        Parameters:
        r - a random number

      • stepG2

        void stepG2(double r)
        Performs actions for G2 phase.

        Cell continue to increase size toward a target of twice its critical size. Cell will transition to M phase after an average time of DURATION_G2. Between G2 and M phase, cell must pass a checkpoint.

        For cells arrested in G2, the transition check for checkpoint recovery occurs after an average time of DURATION_CHECKPOINT.

        Parameters:
        r - a random number

      • stepM

        void stepM(double r,
           ec.util.MersenneTwisterFast random,
           Simulation sim)
        Performs actions for M phase.

        Cell will complete cell division after an average time of DURATION_M.

        Parameters:
        r - a random number
        random - the random number generator
        sim - the simulation instance

      • stepS

        void stepS(double r)
        Performs actions for S phase.

        Cell increases its nuclear size toward a target of twice its critical nuclear size. Cell will transition to G1 phase once nucleus is at least GROWTH_CHECKPOINT_S times the critical nucleus size.

        If cell does not have tags, then cell will transition to G2 phase after an average time of DURATION_S.
